neco - Nodejs Ecosystem COordinator, like virtualenv for python.

<cyan>Usage</cyan>

  neco <command>

Currently where <command> should be one of the below commands:

  <yellow>create</yellow>      -  create new node ecosystem
      Useage: neco create <id> [version]

  <yellow>remove</yellow>      -  removed installed ecosystem
       Usage:  neco remove <id>

  <yellow>list</yellow>        -  list all installed node ecosystem
      Usage:  neco list <id>

  <yellow>update</yellow>      -  update local dist date to latest
      Usage   neco update

  <yellow>find</yellow>        -  find out available node release(s)
      Usage:  neco find [stable, unstable, latest, version]

  <yellow>activate</yellow>    -  show how to activate an existing node ecosystem
      Usage:  neco activate <id>

  <yellow>deactivate</yellow>  -  show how to deactivate an active node ecosystem
      Usage:  neco deactivate <id>

  <yellow>completion</yellow>  -  prints all commands
      Usage:  neco completion

  <yellow>howto</yellow>       -  show usage information
      Usage:  neco howto

